```javascript
const Discord = require('discord.js');
const bot = new Discord.Client();

bot.on('message', message => {
  if (message.content === '/ban') {
    // Handle the command here, such as by sending a message to the user that they have been banned.
  }
});
```
This code uses the "slash" command syntax, which means that the "/" character is used to denote a command, and any arguments that follow are passed to the command as an array. In this case, the "ban" command is handled by the code within the if statement, which sends a message to the user who sent the command indicating that they have been banned.

